Revision history for Perl module Perl5::Build::Warnings

0.07 Fri Jul  3 03:55:29 PM EDT 2026
    - Correction to MANIFEST needed so that test suite can locate file in
      tarball.

0.06 Fri Jul  3 03:14:18 PM EDT 2026
    - No change in functionality -- yet
    - But added a file used in testing and generated via 'make' when building
      a CPAN module.  If this does well on CPANtesters, we will revise the
      documentation to reflect extended usability of this module beyond the Perl 5
      core distribution.
    - In one test stanza, began to explore the possibility of offering the
      user the option to replace "smart quotes" with ordinary double-quotes
      (along the lines suggested by Yves Lubin in a pull request).
    - Accepted https://github.com/jkeenan/perl5-build-warnings/pull/1 from
      Mohammad S Anwar.

0.05 Fri 10 Sep 2021 08:14:54 AM EDT
    - Provide programs with typical usage under examples/

0.04 Thu Dec  5 17:42:24 EST 2019
    - Correct spelling errors in documentation
    - Regenerate README.md with '-t markdown_github'

0.03 Wed Oct 31 18:12:20 EDT 2018
    - Add ability to handle gzip-compressed input files.
    - Add methods get_warnings_for_group() and
      get_warnings_for_source().

0.02 Sat Oct 20 21:11:13 EDT 2018
    - No change in functionality; unneeded import removed

0.01 Sat Oct 20 08:51:04 2018
    - original version; created by ExtUtils::ModuleMaker 0.63


